      <heading>Sun Oct 14 (Cappen)     :: &amp;RNPC Policy Inside the Tower&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>1</slot>
      <level>210</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>
An officer in the Tower Guard may NPC up to three guardsmen at his own
discretion. In emergency situations, he may call upon as many as is 
reasonable. These NPCs will not appear out of thin air. They need time to
arrive. Use common sense. You are all supposed to be excellent RPers, so
I'm sure you'll work it out.

Aes Sedai should not be NPC'd without previous authorization by either
Jaiana or myself EXCEPT in the case of an attack by an obvious male
channeler. Accepted, and even Novices, can be included in a link during
an emergency when one doesnt' have time to wait for calm, stately moving
Aes Sedai to show up and see what all the fuss is about. 13 women would be
more than sufficient whether they have reached the shawl or not. Again,
use common sense. There are over four hundred full Aes Sedai in this Tower
and likely twice that many accepted and light only knows how many novices.
But it still requires time for people to show up when a shout goes out.

Cappen
</text>
    </message>
